Graph generation

% set(groot,'defaultLineLineWidth',2.5)

We want to generate random graphs with specific properties.

Random graphs

Let's first generate a graph with given #nodes and #edges, no self loops and graph connected.
% set options to be able to recompute
seed = 1409;
rng(seed)
% n = input('no. of Nodes')
% e = input('no. of Links')
n = 1000;
e = 1800;
% generate graph with n nodes and e edges
adj = spalloc(n, n, e);
idx = randperm(n * n, e+n);
idx(ismember(idx, 1:n+1:n*n)) = [];
idx = idx(1:e);
% adjacency matrix
adj(idx) = 1;
adj = min( adj + adj.', 1);
adj = full(adj);
% heatmap(matrix)
% heatmap(triu(matrix))
% Deg=sum(matrix)
G = graph(adj);
% get the biggest connected component of G
[bin,binsize] = conncomp(G);%,'Type','weak');
idx = binsize(bin) == max(binsize);
SG = subgraph(G, idx);
% plot the new subgraph
plot(G)
% plot(G,'-.','NodeLabel',{});
plot(SG)
gr = plot(SG,'-.','NodeLabel',{},"Layout","subspace");
embedding1 = [gr.XData' gr.YData'];
gr = plot(SG,'-.','NodeLabel',{},"Layout","force","Iterations",50);
embedding2 = [gr.XData' gr.YData'];

Planar graphs

Generating planar graphs can be done by means of Delaunay triangulation with running time O(n * log(n)). For not to have only triangle faces, we exclude a subset of edges and find the biggest remaining component (see function generateGraphs()).
generateGraphs(0.2,"PlotAll",true);
generateGraphs(0.3);
generateGraphs(0.4);
generateGraphs(0.5);
generateGraphs(0.8);
function [emb_delaunay,emb_force,emb_subspace] = generateGraphs(perc,n,seed,options)
arguments
perc (1,1) double = 0.5
n (1,1) {mustBeInteger,mustBePositive} = 1000
seed (1,1) {mustBeNumeric} = 1409 %392
options.PlotAll (1,1) logical = false
end
% set random seed to be able to recompute
rng(seed)
% generate plot by delaunaytriangulation
dt = delaunayTriangulation(randn(n,2));
emb_delaunay = dt.Points;
% graph from delaunayTriangulation
A = sparse(dt.ConnectivityList, dt.ConnectivityList(:, [2:end 1]), 1);
g = graph(A + A');
% plot the non-sparsified versions
if options.PlotAll
figure
plot(g, '-.','NodeLabel',{},'XData', dt.Points(:, 1), 'YData', dt.Points(:, 2));
title("delaunay")
axis equal
figure
plot(g,'-.','NodeLabel',{},"Layout","force",'Iterations',50);
title("force50")
axis equal
figure
plot(g,'-.','NodeLabel',{},"Layout","subspace");
title("subspace")
axis equal
end
% subset extraction
% remove "perc" percent of edges
e = size(g.Edges,1);
rm_idx = sort(randsample(e,round(e*perc)));
endnodes = g.Edges.EndNodes;
g1 = rmedge(g,endnodes(rm_idx,1),endnodes(rm_idx,2));
% get connected component
[bin,binsize] = conncomp(g1);
idx = binsize(bin) == max(binsize);
sg1 = subgraph(g1, idx);
% plot all unconnected subgraphs
figure
plot(g1,'-.','NodeLabel',{})
title("edge sparsification " + perc)
axis equal
% plot maximum connected subgraphs (mcs)
figure
g_force = plot(sg1,'-.','NodeLabel',{},"Layout","force","Iterations",50);
title("mcs" + perc + " force50")
axis equal
emb_force = [g_force.XData' g_force.YData'];
figure
g_subspace = plot(sg1,'-.','NodeLabel',{},"Layout","subspace");
title("mcs" + perc + " subspace")
axis equal
emb_subspace = [g_subspace.XData' g_subspace.YData'];
end
